</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Genitalia</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Male genitalia of Flospes guangxiensis sp. nov. A dorsal view B lateral view C ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1090.77830.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/663186" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">8A-C</figureCitation>
). Lateral lobes of epiphallus stick-like, apically blunt, and inward curved in dorsal view. Ectoparamere roughly rectangular with the marginal part sclerotized and the remainders membranous. Ectophallic and endophallic apodemes short and not surpass rami.
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/zookeys.1090.77830.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/663184" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" start="Figure 6" startId="F6">
