<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Female</emphasis>
(Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Habitus (alive) of Flospes guangxiensis sp. nov. on a leaf A male B female." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1090.77830.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/663183" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">5B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Habitus photographs of Flospes guangxiensis sp. nov. A male B female. Scale bar: 2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1090.77830.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/663184" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">6B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Flospes guangxiensis sp. nov. A lateral view of male B lateral view of female C male tegmen D female tegmen E face in anterior view F female ovipositor in lateral view G lateral view of hind femur. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1090.77830.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/663185" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">7B, D, F</figureCitation>
). Resembles male but slightly smaller. Longitudinal veins of tegmen parallel and producing rectangular cells (fill with dark brown) with a few pale transverse veins. Ovipositor not surpassing hindwings. Dorsal and ventral margins of the basal of ovipositor smooth and faintly narrowing, and both margins of apical part slightly denticulated and apically curved upwards.
</paragraph>
