<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="113" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="113">
This species is similar in appearance to 
<taxonomicName family="Trigonidiidae" genus="F." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="F. fujianensis" order="Orthoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" rank="species" species="fujianensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">F. fujianensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName family="Trigonidiidae" genus="F." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="F. denutilatus" order="Orthoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" rank="species" species="denutilatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">F. denutilatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs in its squared ectoparamere (that of 
<taxonomicName family="Trigonidiidae" genus="F." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="F. fujianensis" order="Orthoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" rank="species" species="fujianensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">F. fujianensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is round) and blunt apex of epiphallic lateral lobe (that of 
<taxonomicName family="Trigonidiidae" genus="F." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="F. denutilatus" order="Orthoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" rank="species" species="denutilatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">F. denutilatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is acute). The transverse cells of female tegmen of the new are more darker than that of 
<taxonomicName family="Trigonidiidae" genus="F." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="F. fujianensis" order="Orthoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" rank="species" species="fujianensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">F. fujianensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
